Available Tools: escalate_ticket | transfer_to_specialist | get_escalation_status | set_sla
Call Schema: { "func_call": "string", "ticket_id": "string", "reason": "string", "target_team": "string" }
Response Schema: { "ticket_id": "string", "escalated_to": "string", "reason": "string", "sla_hours": number, "status": "string" }
---
Question: Set a 4-hour SLA for ticket TKT-2045 concerning the inventory sync failure and assign it to the Supply Chain Logistics team.
Call: { "func_call": "set_sla", "ticket_id": "TKT-2045", "reason": "Inventory sync failure causing stock discrepancies", "target_team": "Supply Chain Logistics" }
Response: { "ticket_id": "TKT-2045", "escalated_to": "Supply Chain Logistics", "reason": "Inventory sync failure causing stock discrepancies", "sla_hours": 4, "status": "SLA_ACTIVE" }

Question: Check the current escalation status for ticket TKT-3198 which was transferred to the Fraud Prevention unit this morning.
Call: { "func_call": "get_escalation_status", "ticket_id": "TKT-3198", "reason": "Status update on flagged fraudulent transaction review", "target_team": "Fraud Prevention" }
Response: { "ticket_id": "TKT-3198", "escalated_to": "Fraud Prevention", "reason": "Status update on flagged fraudulent transaction review", "sla_hours": 12, "status": "IN_REVIEW" }

